-- 
RWE Unit Essent to Install Amsterdam Electric Vehicle Charging Stations

-- B y   L o u i s e   D o w n i n g
-- 
2011-04-15T12:02:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/rwe-unit-essent-to-install-amsterdam-electric-vehicle-charging-stations.html
Essent NV, a unit of  Germany ’s
second-largest utility  RWE AG (RWE) , won a contract to supply and
install at least 125 electric-vehicle charging stations in
Amsterdam.  Essent was awarded the contract from the Amsterdam City
Council, which is planning for 10,000 electric vehicles by 2015,
according to a  statement  today on Essen, Germany-based RWE’s
website. The city already has about 100 charging points.  RWE may eventually install as many as 750 charging stations
in Amsterdam, it said. Its first are due to be installed by
June.  “The charging stations we are setting up in Amsterdam have
been developed by RWE and have so far been installed in numerous
European countries, including Germany, Poland, Hungary and
 Austria ,” Peter Terium, chief executive officer of Essent, said
in the statement.  RWE currently operates more than 800 charging stations in
14 European countries, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
